{"key":"processedPost-15582171","value":{"id":15582171,"first":15581943,"last":15670193,"when":1325090674,"utime":"12/28/11 06:44 PM","content":"With a reservoir, it's important not to fill it too often.&nbsp; The cake must begin to dry out and lose moisture, and then you 'water' it to replace that moisture.&nbsp; Avoid filling the reservoir every day because a waterlogged cake will perform as poorly as one which is too dry, but both will produce small, stunted fruits, often confusing the issue.<br /><br />You can learn to judge water content by gently lifting each cake to feel for the weight.&nbsp; If it's heavy, don't fill the reservoir or dunk.<br />RR","title":"Re: Crusty white on caps? Something wrong here? *PIC*","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}